{
  "texts": [
    "The C2fLEFEM module is responsible for enhancing feature semantic information.",
    "Figure 2 depicts a specific structure diagram.",
    "The C2fLEFEM module, as shown in Fig. 2, is composed of three sub-modules: the Low Frequency Filter Enhancement Module (LEF), the Feature Enhancement Module (FEM), and the C2f module.",
    "To begin, the LEF module applies low-frequency filtering to the input features in order to remove high-frequency noise.",
    "The FEM module then accepts the low-frequency enhanced features and the original features as dual inputs and keeps the original low-frequency semantic information while reducing high-frequency noise through a series of procedures."
  ]
}